**Memory File Format (every `.md` file in this directory):**

```markdown
---
name: short-kebab-case-slug
description: one-line summary — used to decide relevance during recall
type: user | feedback | project | reference
---

The fact or rule. For feedback/project memories, follow with **Why:** and **How to apply:** lines.
Link related memories with [[their-name]].
```

**Note:** The `type` field is a top-level frontmatter key, NOT wrapped in a `metadata:` block. This matches the format used by all existing memory files.

**Creation threshold:** Create a new file when the fact introduces a new rule, decision, or architectural pattern. Append to an existing file when adding a new instance or session note to an existing category.

**Stale-marker convention:** When verifying a memory against current code and finding it outdated, prepend `(STALE — verified [date])` to the description field and update the body with corrected information.

