## 7. Known Conflicts & Gotchas

| Issue | Root Cause | Resolution |
|-------|------------|------------|
| **Status line shows `auto mode on` instead of custom bar** | Windows backslashes in `statusLine.command` are treated as escape sequences by the internal Git Bash runner | Always use forward slashes (`C:/Users/...`) in both global and project `settings.json` |
| **Status line still not showing after editing settings** | `statusLine` config is cached at process startup | Full restart of Claude Code is required after any `statusLine` change |
| **Trust dialog repeats on every session** | `hasTrustDialogAccepted` is missing from `~/.claude.json` | Accept the dialog once interactively; do not try to hand-edit `.claude.json` |
| **SessionStart hook fails with "node not found"** | Hook runs before shell env is fully initialized | Ensure Node.js is in your **system** PATH, not just user PATH |
| **post-tool-use hook crashes silently** | `.remember/logs/` directory missing | Create it in Section 4.1; the hook tries to auto-create it but may race |
| **Memory save time shows `—` forever** | No `.md` files in memory directory yet | The timer appears once the first memory file is written by an agent |
| **Plugins not available** | Marketplace not initialized or plugin IDs changed | Run `/plugin list` and `/plugin install <name>` manually; IDs may drift |
| **`.cjs` vs `.js` confusion** | Project may later declare `"type": "module"` | Any file using `require()` must use `.cjs` extension |
| **"permissionMode" rejected by validation** | `"permissionMode": "yesToAll"` is not a valid schema field | Use `"permissions": { "defaultMode": "auto" }` instead |
| **Lost all configs after reinstall** | `~/.claude/` and `project/.claude/` are machine-specific and not in Git | Back up `~/.claude/settings.json`, `~/.claude/3dastroids-statusline.cjs`, and `project/.claude/` to a private dotfiles repo or cloud storage |

**Engine-specific gotchas will be appended here as they are discovered.**

